==Awards==
The awards and all-star teams are as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.curling.ca/2012/02/25/all-stars-and-sportsmanship-winner-declared-at-2012-scotties-tournament-of-hearts/|title=All Stars and Sportsmanship Winner Declared at 2012 Scotties Tournament of Hearts|date=25 February 2012|publisher=[[Canadian Curling Association]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.curling.ca/blog/2012/02/26/heather-nedohin-named-mvp-at-2012-scotties-tournament-of-hearts/|title=Heather Nedohin named MVP at 2012 Scotties Tournament of Hearts|date=26 February 2012|publisher=[[Canadian Curling Association]]}}</ref>

;[[Sandra Schmirler Most Valuable Player Award]]
* {{flagicon|AB}} [[Heather Nedohin]], Alberta

;[[Scotties Tournament of Hearts Shot of the Week Award|Shot of the Week Award]]
* {{flagicon|BC}} [[Sasha Carter]], British Columbia

;[[Marj Mitchell Sportsmanship Award]]
* {{flagicon|ON}} [[Amanda Gates]], Ontario 

;All-Star Teams
''First Team''
* Skip: {{flagicon|MB}} [[Jennifer Jones (curler)|Jennifer Jones]], Manitoba
* Third: {{flagicon|MB}} [[Kaitlyn Lawes]], Manitoba
* Second: {{flagicon|MB}} [[Jill Officer]], Manitoba
* Lead: {{flagicon|MB}} [[Dawn Askin]], Manitoba

''Second Team''
* Skip: {{flagicon|BC}} [[Kelly Scott]], British Columbia
* Third: {{flagicon|AB}} [[Beth Iskiw]], Alberta
* Second: {{flagicon|AB}} [[Jessica Mair]], Alberta
* Lead: {{flagicon|AB}} [[Laine Peters]], Alberta

